snippet.textDisplay:
I recently started raising chickens and I’m seriously heartbroken now. I don’t think I can eat meat anymore after this video.

My little baby chicks are about 6 weeks and have double or tripled in size since I first got them. They are so cute and scramble around looking for worms that I throw out. they get so excited and scared for having the other chicks take it that as soon as they find a worm they spring off into a corner. I basically just wanted the chicks as pets and for eggs eventually, but seeing how big this chicken was really makes me sad that it died. Because I imagine all the time it spent scrambling around trying to protect itself and it’s life. This creature didn’t want to die. They are afraid of every sound and continue eating, so they clearly want to keep living :( I guess I never really cared before because meat is tasty, but I’m not sure I can continue eating it now.
